This paper is about trust management, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses distributed systems and access control, which are topics in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of logic programming for policy specification suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the termination of computations, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
